Software programs are used to encrypt files, folders and even entire drives.

Encrypting File System (EFS) is a Windows feature that can encrypt data
directly linked to a specific user account and only the user that encrypts the data will be able to access it

STEPS IN HOW TO ENCRYPT DATA USING EFS
SELECT FOLDER
RIGHT CLICK-PROPERTIES
CLICK ADVANCED
SELECT ENCRYPT CONTENTS TO SECURE DATA 
FILES AND FOLDERS THAT HAVE BEEN ENCRYPTED WITH EFS ARE DISPLAYED IN GREEN 
